'''[[Rosetta]]''' is the anglicised name of the city of Rashid, Egypt, famous as the location of the [[Rosetta Stone]].
'''Rosetta''' may also refer to:
As a '''placename''': * [[Rosetta, Belfast]] in Northern Ireland * [[Rosetta, Tasmania]], suburb of Hobart, Tasmania, Australia
In '''entertainment''': * [[Rosetta (band)]], an American post-metal band formed in 2003 * [[Rosetta (film)|''Rosetta'' (film)]], a 1999 Belgian film * [[Rosetta (novel)|''Rosetta'' (novel)]], a Star Trek: Enterprise novel * ''[[Rosetta: The Masked Angel]]'' (''Kamen Tenshi Rosetta''), a Japanese toku series that aired in 1998 * Rosetta, the Japanese name of Rosalina, a character in the video game ''[[Super Mario Galaxy]]'' * Rosetta Passel, a character in [[Kaleido Star#Characters|''Kaleido Star'']] anime series * [[Sister Rosetta Tharpe]] a pioneering singer of gospel and Rock and Roll
In '''bioscience''': * [[Rosetta Biosoftware]], a subsidiary of Merck & Co. * [[Rosetta Genomics]], a molecular diagnostics company * [[Rosetta@home]], a freeware program available to help predict and design protein structures
In '''natural language''': * [[Rosetta Project]], a global collaboration which collects and archives languages in danger of extinction
In '''computing''': * [[Rosetta (software)]], a software emulator developed by Transitive Corp. for Apple Computer * Rosetta, a web-based translation application written by [[Canonical Ltd.]] for use on the Linux distribution Ubuntu operating system * Rosetta<!-- [http://www.handhelds.org/project/rosetta/] -->, a handwriting recognition system for the [[OpenZaurus]] palmtop operating system * [[Newton_OS#Handwriting_recognition|Rosetta]], the Apple Newton's handwriting recognition system * [[RosettaNet]], a standardisation proposal for commercial information * Rosetta, the Microsoft codename of [[SQL Server Reporting Services]]
In '''science''': * [[Rosetta (spacecraft)]], a European Space Agency-led craft launched in 2004 to study comet 67P/Churyumov-Gerasimenko * [[Rosetta (orbit)]], a type of orbit seen in spherically symmetric but not <math>1/r</math> potentials
In '''other uses''': * ''Rosetta'', a synonym for the Italian wine grape [[Nebbiolo]] * A form of [[latte art]] which resembles a flower * [[rosetta (bread)|An alternative denomination]] of the [[michetta]] bread.
== See also == * [[Rosetta Stone (disambiguation)]] * [[Rosette (disambiguation)]], a flower-like shape
